    div.legal-container
      h1 Privacy Policy for Ian's Sudoku Challenge
      p Last Updated: Apr 25, 2026
      
      p Welcome to Ian's Sudoku Challenge. We believe in keeping games simple and private. This Privacy Policy explains our commitment to your privacy and how the app operates on your device.

      h2 1. Data Collection and Storage
      p Ian's Sudoku Challenge is built to run entirely locally.
      ul
        li #[strong Local Storage:] All of your game progress, settings, and high scores are stored directly on your physical device. We do not operate any databases or servers to store your game data.
        li #[strong No Accounts:] You do not need to sign in, provide an email, or create an account to play the game.
        li #[strong No Developer Access:] We have absolutely no way to see, access, or retrieve your gameplay data. What happens on your device stays on your device.

      h2 2. Advertising and Third-Party Services
      p To help support the development of this free game, we use third-party advertising services.
      ul
        li #[strong Google AdMob:] We use Google AdMob to display banner ads and rewarded video ads. While we do not collect any data ourselves, AdMob may collect and use certain information (such as advertising IDs and basic device usage data) to serve and measure the performance of these ads.
        li You can learn more about how Google uses information from apps that use their services by visiting Google's Privacy & Terms site.

      h2 3. Tracking and Analytics
      p We respect your privacy and minimize tracking.
      ul
        li #[strong No Location Tracking:] We do not ask for, track, or collect your physical location data.
        li #[strong No Telemetry:] Aside from the necessary data collected by Google AdMob to serve ads, we do not use third-party analytics software or behavioral trackers. 

      h2 4. Managing and Deleting Your Data
      p Because your data lives exclusively on your hardware, you retain total control over it. You can permanently delete all your game data at any time by:
      ul
        li Using the "Delete All Data" option located in the app's settings menu.
        li Clearing the app's local data within your device's operating system settings.
        li Uninstalling the application from your device.
      
      h2 5. Changes to This Policy
      p If we update our practices or add new features, we will update this policy accordingly to maintain total transparency.

      h2 Contact Information
      p If you have any questions regarding this privacy policy or the app, please contact:
